Introduction In this article, we will try to setup password-less login using ssh keys to connect to remote Linux servers without entering a password.
open your preferred terminal and follow the steps:
Generate Authentication Keys on local machine ssh-keygen -t rsa Create .ssh Directory on remote machine ssh &lt;user&gt;@&lt;remote-ip-adress&gt; mkdir -p .ssh Upload Generated Public Keys to remote machine cat .ssh/id_rsa.pub | ssh &lt;user&gt;@&lt;remote-ip-adress&gt; &#39;cat &gt;&gt; ~/.ssh/authorized_keys&#39; Login to remote machine ssh &lt;user&gt;@&lt;remote-ip-adress&gt;
